00:02:29.690 --> 00:02:36.360
Okay. If you think
about May of 1961,

00:02:36.360 --> 00:02:40.540
John F. Kennedy was petitioning
Congress to send a human being.

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:42.170
He said a man, the
man space program.

00:02:42.170 --> 00:02:46.270
But I always change it to human
because when we say the language

00:02:46.270 --> 00:02:50.220
of a man space program, when I go
into schools and I ask the kids,

00:02:50.220 --> 00:02:53.280
who wants to be an astronaut
and say man space program,

00:02:53.280 --> 00:02:55.670 position:56%
none of the girls raise their hands.

00:02:55.670 --> 00:02:57.990
So the language is so important.

00:02:57.990 --> 00:03:00.620
So the human space program
he was petitioning Congress

00:03:00.620 --> 00:03:06.130
for to send people to the moon
and back safely in May of 1961.

00:03:06.130 --> 00:03:11.110
At the same time, Dr. Martin Luther
King Jr. was going to the south

00:03:11.110 --> 00:03:13.860
to console the Freedom Riders
that were getting bombed.

00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:16.790
We were having the most
technologically advanced thing

00:03:16.790 --> 00:03:20.490
happening potentially in
the, in less than 10 years.

00:03:20.490 --> 00:03:21.790
And we were not even be able

00:03:21.790 --> 00:03:24.840
to get our civil rights
straight here in our country.

00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:29.860
And I think about during
that same time in the 60's,

00:03:29.860 --> 00:03:35.700
