00:04:04.700 --> 00:04:11.090
She went to a NAACP meeting in Los
Angeles and bumped into someone

00:04:11.090 --> 00:04:13.980
who said they were
her number one fan.

00:04:13.980 --> 00:04:18.810
That number one fan was Dr. Martin
Luther King Jr. He was like,

00:04:18.810 --> 00:04:21.990
oh my God it is Nichelle
Nichols [laughter].

00:04:21.990 --> 00:04:26.540
And she saw his enthusiasm
for the show.

00:04:26.540 --> 00:04:30.820
He even said, this is the only show
that I will let my kids stay up

00:04:30.820 --> 00:04:33.180
and watch at night
because you are doing

00:04:33.180 --> 00:04:36.690
with Star Trek what I am trying to
do with the Civil Rights Movement.

00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:39.350
She tore up her resignation
and she stayed with the show.

00:04:39.350 --> 00:04:42.410
And NASA hired Nichelle to
bring in the first women

00:04:42.410 --> 00:04:43.980
and minorities as astronauts.

00:04:43.980 --> 00:04:46.530
She was on a contract to do that.

00:04:46.530 --> 00:04:51.440
Guy Bluford, Mae Jemison,
Sally Ride were all products

00:04:51.440 --> 00:04:57.560
