Yes sir?

00:38:40.040 --> 00:38:43.810
&gt;&gt; What was your favorite
thing about going to space?

00:38:43.810 --> 00:38:46.540
&gt;&gt; Leland Melvin: The favorite
thing about going to space.

00:38:46.540 --> 00:38:47.910
It was not the bathroom,
okay [laughter].

00:38:47.910 --> 00:38:52.470
And I have a story about
that later if you want to.

00:38:52.470 --> 00:38:55.290
It is really hard to go
to the bathroom in space.

00:38:55.290 --> 00:38:58.740
I think the favorite thing
was looking out the window

00:38:58.740 --> 00:39:03.290
with my colleagues that I was
work-in with from around the world

00:39:03.290 --> 00:39:06.970
and to fly over Lynchburg,
Virginia, my hometown,

00:39:06.970 --> 00:39:10.600
and think about my parents and
family having a meal down there.

00:39:10.600 --> 00:39:11.900
Five minutes.

00:39:11.900 --> 00:39:16.300
Okay. Having a meal down there and
then seven minutes later we are

00:39:16.300 --> 00:39:20.040
over Paris and Leo is
looking down thinking

00:39:20.040 --> 00:39:21.660
about his family having a meal.

00:39:21.660 --> 00:39:24.010
And Yuri is looking off to Russia.

00:39:24.010 --> 00:39:29.730
So we are all experiencing seeing
our hometowns from space in a very,

00:39:29.730 --> 00:39:31.620
very short period of time.

00:39:31.620 --> 00:39:34.310 position:56%
And then a little bit later you are
back around the planet and if I were

00:39:34.310 --> 00:39:37.220
in Virginia, I am not in
Tennessee and I am stepping

00:39:37.220 --> 00:39:41.460
across the United States in
this very short period of time.

00:39:41.460 --> 00:39:42.800 position:56%
And then also playing with your food

00:39:42.800 --> 00:39:45.260
in space is really
cool too [laughter].

00:39:45.260 --> 00:39:46.560
Good question.

00:39:46.560 --> 00:39:47.860
